<br>
&quot;I wish to, at this time, offer my apoligies to the people within this room.  I know you are here because you probably wish to see a large dramatic fight, and I do suppose I am helping to give you what you want, I do not feel this single rant offers a proper representation of myself and my feelings.<br>
<br>
I consider myself to be a very good person.  I try very hard to work for others before myself.  I try very hard to help people out with their problems.  As it relates to this situation, I had stayed with Resolution for a full month after I normally would have wished to leave because I felt that I had a duty to help make things better.  (this was noted in my first farewell)<br>
<br>
I felt when I left that certain happenings had pushed myself over the edge into making the descion that was right for me.  Since I have left, I have found problems arising that drag me to an even deeper state of frustration.  I honestly feel that my actions in leaving were done with the best intentions. I honestly believe that I said was done out of the respect I felt my friends deserved for their future, even if the people who read them still disagree.<br>
<br>
Since then, I have found many who I once considered good friends, or even people who I still think are good friends, hate myself on a very personal level.  I am well aware that the adventures we all have in the land of Norrath do not last forever, and are viewed as a game by many, but that does not mean the friendships we forge are meaningless, and I do become saddened when they are so harshly cut off due to political differences.<br>
<br>
I do not apoligize for my attitude that is directed toward Aailin, nor do I apoligize for the words I have written.  I am sorry that I have given everyone here such a poor representation of my true self.  I am sorry that I am now acting in such a way that most people thought I was not capable of and if I have disappointed people.  My only reasoning is that a kind person can only be pushed so far before something snaps within, and that I have felt something snap.<br>
<br>
Resolution is a band of very fine people, and I do not believe they are being properly represented here either.  Thus far Aailin has spoken for them, but I will point out that no others have come forth with words of their own in the matter.  I do not know how many agree with him, but I would ugre you to give each individual the benefit of doubt and allow them to make impressions for themselves.&quot;<br>
